[If further studies show that infection with _Plasmodium simium_ is indeed common, perhaps _P. simium_ should be considered a human parasite just as _Plasmodium knowlesi_ is now regarded to be a human parasite. Also, for _P. knowlesi_, it was genetic analysis that showed that what was previously thought to be _P. malariae_ was indeed _P. knowlesi_.

Based on the finding described here, larger genetic studies of presumed _P. vivax_ in Brazil are needed. ProMED will be happy to post more information on simian malaria in Brazil. - Mod.EP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4911401,6.]
